div.p:
Dobrynin’s agenda for lunchReference is to Rostow’s lunch meeting with Dobrynin on November 14. was quite clear:
—Vietnam;
—missile talks.

item.p:
Missile talks. I told him that there might be advantages in
                                    opening the missile talks soon; but two things would be required
                                    if the President could have a strong case: 

—an atmosphere that made such talks politically
                                            possible;

—clarity about the result.
